5000|$|EU <b>Cohesion</b> <b>Policy</b> {{is a new}} reform {{programme}} {{which has}} been developed to assess and monitor the evaluation of Structural Funds and their outcome in lower developing regions. The new reform {{became one of the}} most intensively evaluated policies in Europe. The contributors and assessors are policy makers and researchers from different range of disciplines. EU <b>Cohesion</b> <b>Policy</b> refers to the set of activities aimed to reduction of regional and social disparities in the European Union. Although, the EU <b>Cohesion</b> <b>Policy</b> appears as a relatively well designated programme, there are still some unresolved issues in terms of measurements, philosophical approaches and methods of <b>Cohesion</b> <b>Policy</b> evaluation.|$|E
